Billionaire’s daughter Temi Otedola has stated her preference for a private wedding. In a question and answer session with her musician fiance Mr Eazi, the duo agreed that they prefer a much confined wedding to a gathering of large crowds. Mr Eazi referred to his sister’s wedding and how he didn’t even know most of the people that came for the event.   Alma Mata honours Comedian Bovi     I’m not afraid of giving love another chance –…     ‘Stefflon the best woman Burna Boy will ever…   The billionaire daughter revealed that she would be angry if she does not know any of the attendees at her wedding, which is why she prefers a very private wedding. She saId: “Knowing me, if I’m walking around my wedding and I’m like “I don’t know this person”, that will annoy me. I’m really private. Like even for a birthday party, everyone there I have to rock with you. “If it were up to me, my wedding will just be family and five friends. Sorry, a lot of you are going to be upset but, it’s gonna be tight.”